{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771335742,"nonce":"72JHcEZiVJjOghSKQIQsISv70Go=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87rm3_C","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/215","origin":"github"},"title":"build_report_generator.py shows 0 packages due to ast.literal_eval failure on OrderedDict","message":"## Bug\n\nThe build report generated by `build_report_generator.py` shows `0 (OK: 0)` for every layer despite packages building successfully. Package names appear in the \"Output\" column (from stderr parsing) but aren't counted.\n\n## Root Cause\n\n`parse_log_line()` uses `ast.literal_eval()` to parse colcon event log data. However, colcon's `JobQueued` events contain `OrderedDict()` function calls in the data dict:\n\n```\n[0.000458] (camp) JobQueued: {'identifier': 'camp', 'dependencies': OrderedDict()}\n```\n\n`ast.literal_eval()` rejects function calls by design, raising `ValueError`. The exception is caught by a bare `except Exception: return None`, silently discarding the line. Since `JobQueued` is the event that populates the `packages` set, no packages are ever counted.\n\n## Fix\n\nDecouple line parsing (pkg_name + event_type extraction) from data dict parsing. Only attempt `ast.literal_eval()` for event types that need it (`JobEnded` for the `rc` field). `JobQueued` and `StderrLine` only need the package name, which is already extracted from the line prefix.\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}